occurrenceRemarks: Tree, 30m x 75cm diameter. Trunk sligthly buttressed to 0,5 m high. Bark red-brown, not fissured but prominently lenticellate. Slash red with deep red sap, wood red-brown. Fruit brown with faint grey lenticels. Kernel of fruit eaten locally & crushed to add to tapioca cakes (beijú), oil used lacally for cooking and soap.
